### Security Requirements

**Non-negotiable defaults (keep these, add project-specific rules below):**

- All API routes MUST require authentication unless explicitly marked public
- Never commit secrets, .env files, or API keys
- RLS MUST be enabled on all database tables (Supabase: `ALTER TABLE ... ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`)
- Validate all user input at API boundaries (Zod, joi, or equivalent)
- Use parameterized queries — never concatenate user input into SQL
- Return generic error messages to clients — log details server-side only
- Never expose stack traces, internal paths, or DB schema in error responses
- Run `npm audit` (or equivalent) before every deploy

